        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 6:57PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 657 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Floris, or 12 miles west of Beaver, moving east at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Beaver, Forgan, Elmwood, Bryans Corner, Boyd, Mocane, Turpin, Floris,
and Balko.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
